para.para:
svg_color has a constructor for svg_color_constant, so you can use a svg_color_constant in place of a svg_color and it will be implicitly converted. However, there is not currently an svg_color::operator=(svg_color_constant) overload, so
svg_color my_color = red;
does not have the desired effect, and nor does cout << red << endl; output the expected RGB(255,0,0) but instead 119 the value of the enum!

section.para:


my_plot.write("simple.svg");

          This writes our plot to the file "simple.svg". SVG files can
          be viewed with most browsers, or embedded into documents.

